{{fr-adj}}

# {{lb|fr|grammar}} [[causative]]; [[factitive]] (said of a [[verb]] where the subject is made to do the action)
#: {{ux|fr|Il faut distinguer forme '''factitive''' du verbe et son sens '''factitif'''. Ainsi, un verbe comme « construire » peut être employé dans un sens '''factitif''': Pierre construit une maison en banlieue. [Il la construit lui-même, ou il la fait construire, selon le cas].|It is necessary to distinguish between the '''factitive''' form of the verb and its '''factitive''' meaning. In this way, a verb such as “construire” can be used in a '''factitive''' sense: Pierre is building a house in the suburbs. [He builds it himself, or he has it built, depending on the case].}}

{{fr-noun|m}}

# {{lb|fr|grammar}} [[causative]]; [[factitive]] ([[verbal]] [[mode]] where the subject causes the action to be done)
#: {{ux|fr|Le '''factitif''' s’applique à un verbe transitif et indique que le sujet fait effectuer une action par un autre agent que lui-même.|The '''factitive''' applies itself to a transitive verb and indicates that the subject has an action performed by an agent other than itself.}}
